recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2015-2019 Ford F-150 and 2017-2019 Ford F-250 Super Duty, F-350 Super Duty, F-450 Super Duty, and F-550 Super Duty pick-up trucks equipped with an engine block heater.   Water and contaminants may get into the block heater cable's splice connector causing corrosion and damage.
recalls.Consequence: When the heater is plugged in, prolonged corrosion could cause a resistive short, increasing the risk of overheated or melted wiring which can increase the risk of a fire.
recalls.Remedy: Ford will notify owners, and dealers will disable the block heater cable, free of charge.  Once parts are available, Dealers will replace the engine block heater cable, free of charge.  The recall began June 3, 2019.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 18S45.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2015-2017 F-150, and 2017 F-250, F-350, F-450, and F-550 vehicles originally produced with black or body colored exterior door handles that may have been subsequently equipped with a chrome exterior door handle cover accessory kit purchased from a Ford dealer.  These accessory door handle covers may cause the doors to unlatch in a side impact collision.  As such, these vehicles may fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard (FMVSS) number 206, "Door Locks and Door Retention Components."
recalls.Consequence: If the doors unlatch and open in a side impact collision, the occupants have an increased risk of injury.
recalls.Remedy: Ford will notify owners, and dealers will remove the accessory covers and refund the purchase price.  The recall began July 13, 2017.  Owners may contact Ford at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for the recall is 17C09.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

issues.title: EGR Cooler Failure
issues.description: The EGR cooler develops cracks or internal failures, causing coolant to leak into the intake system and potentially leading to catastrophic engine damage if coolant enters the cylinders.
issues.fix_description: Replace EGR cooler assembly and associated gaskets. Some owners opt for EGR delete kits where legally permitted.
issues.prevention: Regular coolant changes, monitor coolant levels frequently, address cooling system issues promptly

issues.title: CP4 Fuel Injection Pump Failure
issues.description: The high-pressure CP4 fuel injection pump experiences catastrophic failure, sending metal debris throughout the entire fuel system and contaminating injectors, fuel lines, and tank.
issues.fix_description: Complete fuel system replacement including pump, injectors, lines, tank cleaning, and fuel rail. Often requires engine removal.
issues.prevention: Use high-quality diesel fuel, change fuel filters regularly, consider aftermarket CP3 pump conversion

issues.title: Turbocharger Failure
issues.description: Turbocharger experiences bearing failure, compressor wheel damage, or actuator problems, leading to reduced power and potential engine damage from debris.
issues.fix_description: Replace turbocharger assembly, inspect and clean intake system, replace oil and filter
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with quality oil, allow engine to cool down before shutdown, avoid aggressive driving when cold

issues.title: DEF System Issues
issues.description: Diesel Exhaust Fluid system components including pumps, sensors, and lines fail causing reduced power mode and inability to restart after shutdown.
issues.fix_description: Replace faulty DEF pump, lines, or sensors. Reset system with scan tool.
issues.prevention: Use only quality DEF fluid, keep tank filled above 1/4, avoid letting system run completely empty

issues.title: Transmission Harsh Shifting
issues.description: The 6R140 transmission exhibits harsh shifting, delayed engagement, and premature wear of internal components, particularly in higher mileage vehicles.
issues.fix_description: Transmission rebuild or replacement, update transmission software, replace transmission fluid and filter
issues.prevention: Regular transmission service every 30k miles, avoid excessive towing in extreme heat, use proper transmission fluid

issues.title: Cooling System Leaks
issues.description: Various cooling system components including radiator, water pump, and coolant hoses develop leaks leading to overheating and potential engine damage.
issues.fix_description: Replace leaking components such as radiator, water pump, hoses, or thermostats
issues.prevention: Regular coolant changes, inspect hoses for wear, monitor coolant levels, flush cooling system per schedule

issues.title: DPF Clogging Issues
issues.description: Diesel Particulate Filter becomes clogged with soot, especially in vehicles used primarily for short trips or city driving, causing regeneration issues.
issues.fix_description: Professional DPF cleaning or replacement, forced regeneration, repair any upstream issues causing excessive soot
issues.prevention: Regular highway driving for passive regeneration, use low-ash oil, don't interrupt active regeneration cycles

issues.title: Fuel Rail Pressure Sensor Failure
issues.description: Fuel rail pressure sensors fail causing incorrect fuel pressure readings, leading to poor engine performance, rough idle, and potential fuel system damage.
issues.fix_description: Replace fuel rail pressure sensor, clear codes, verify proper fuel pressure readings
issues.prevention: Use quality fuel, change fuel filters regularly, avoid running fuel tank too low

issues.title: Air Filter Restriction Issues
issues.description: Air filter housing design allows debris bypass and premature clogging, leading to reduced airflow and turbocharger damage over time.
issues.fix_description: Replace air filter, inspect housing for damage, consider upgraded air filter system
issues.prevention: Regular air filter inspections and changes, especially in dusty conditions

issues.title: Battery and Charging Issues
issues.description: Dual battery system experiences premature battery failure, alternator issues, or charging system problems causing electrical system failures.
issues.fix_description: Replace batteries, test alternator output, repair charging system wiring as needed
issues.prevention: Regular battery testing, avoid extended idle periods, keep terminals clean and tight

issues.title: FICM Power Supply Issues
issues.description: Fuel Injection Control Module power supply fails, causing erratic injector operation, rough running, and potential no-start conditions, particularly in cold weather.
issues.fix_description: Replace FICM or repair internal power supply, update software if available
issues.prevention: Block heater use in cold weather, avoid extended idle periods, maintain proper battery voltage

issues.title: Exhaust Gas Recirculation Valve Sticking
issues.description: EGR valve becomes stuck open or closed due to carbon buildup, affecting engine performance and emissions compliance.
issues.fix_description: Clean or replace EGR valve, clean intake manifold, update engine software
issues.prevention: Regular highway driving, quality fuel use, periodic EGR system cleaning

editorial.hero_blurb: The F-250 Power Stroke represents the pinnacle of American heavy-duty capability, combining Ford's legendary truck DNA with a sophisticated 6.7L diesel that delivers crushing torque. This isn't just transportation—it's a statement of serious intent.
editorial.essence: The F-250 Power Stroke transforms brute force into refined capability, offering an intoxicating blend of raw diesel power and modern refinement. It's the truck that makes light work of heavy tasks while delivering surprising comfort and technology.
editorial.heritage: Born from Ford's Super Duty lineage that dates back to 1999, the F-250 carries forward decades of commercial-grade engineering. The 6.7L Power Stroke diesel, introduced in 2011, represents Ford's commitment to in-house diesel development after partnerships with International and Navistar.
editorial.design_philosophy: Ford's engineers prioritized maximum capability without compromise, creating a platform that could handle the most demanding commercial applications while serving as a premium personal vehicle. Every component was engineered for durability, from the high-strength steel frame to the robust drivetrain.
editorial.motorsport_history: While not a traditional racing platform, the F-250 has dominated commercial vehicle competitions and endurance challenges, proving its mettle in grueling real-world conditions that matter more than lap times.
editorial.engine_character: The 6.7L Power Stroke delivers its massive torque with diesel authority—a rumbling, relentless surge that builds from idle and maintains strength throughout the rev range. It's an engine that feels unstoppable, with turbo whistle providing the soundtrack to serious capability.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 6-speed automatic shifts with deliberate precision, holding gears under load and delivering smooth, confident shifts that complement the diesel's torque curve. Downshifts arrive with satisfying authority when towing demands arise.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Built on a fully boxed frame with heavy-duty suspension, the F-250 delivers truck-like solidity with surprising composure. The ride is firm but controlled, communicating road surface while maintaining stability under any load condition.
editorial.steering_feel: Steering is appropriately weighted for a heavy-duty truck, offering good on-center feel and predictable response. While not sports car precise, it provides the confidence needed when maneuvering large loads or navigating tight work sites.
editorial.brake_confidence: Massive brakes provide impressive stopping power for such a substantial vehicle, with excellent pedal feel and fade resistance even under heavy towing conditions. The system inspires confidence when hauling maximum loads down mountain grades.
editorial.sound_signature: The Power Stroke announces itself with a purposeful diesel rumble at idle, building to an authoritative roar under acceleration. Turbo whistle and exhaust note combine to create an unmistakably industrial symphony that diesel enthusiasts crave.
editorial.ideal_owner: Serious work truck users, heavy towing enthusiasts, and diesel aficionados who need maximum capability with modern refinement. Perfect for contractors, RV towers, and those who refuse to compromise on capability.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Casual drivers who rarely utilize the truck's capabilities, those seeking maximum fuel economy, or buyers who prioritize car-like ride quality over work truck functionality.
editorial.buyers_summary: Focus on 2020+ models for the latest refinements and improved emissions systems. Higher trim levels offer impressive luxury while maintaining work truck capability, making them excellent daily drivers for serious truck users.

expertReviews.title: The 2025 Ford F-250 Super Duty Lariat Is A Monstrous Diesel Truck With Torque For Days
pros: Best-in-class 500 horsepower and 1,200 ft-lbs of torque from high-output Power Stroke diesel
Impressive towing capacity up to 22,000 lbs (40,000 lbs on F-450)
Strong payload capacity of 3,669 lbs
Black appearance package provides attractive sinister look
Premium ActiveX synthetic leather seating material
Pro Power onboard with 2kW output capability
Rolling tonneau cover and spray-in bedliner add utility
cons: $13,500 premium for high-output diesel engine option
Front air dam reduces ground clearance
Lariat trim still uses incandescent tail lights instead of full LED
Bulky and cheap-feeling key fob design
Massive size makes maneuvering challenging
expertReviews.verdict: The 2025 Ford F-250 Super Duty Lariat maintains its position as the numbers king in the heavy-duty truck segment with class-leading power and capability. The high-output Power Stroke diesel delivers exceptional torque for serious towing needs, while the black appearance package and ActiveX interior materials add premium touches. Despite the high cost of diesel option and some minor design compromises, this truck remains the go-to choice for those who need maximum capability.

expertReviews.title: 2025 Ford F-250 Lariat with 6.7L Powerstroke Turbo Diesel
pros: Excellent ventilated seats with strong fans
10-speed transmission shifts smoothly with diesel
Commanding high driving position
Light steering assistance makes maneuvering easy despite size
Spacious luxurious interior with panoramic sunroof
Strong turbo diesel performance
Comprehensive tech features including heads-up display and 360 camera
cons: Manual tilt and telescoping steering wheel
Rear windows are manual up/down only
Large size requires careful attention to clearances
expertReviews.verdict: The 2025 Ford F-250 Lariat with 6.7L PowerStroke diesel impresses with its combination of luxury and capability. The reviewer particularly praised the smooth 10-speed transmission, excellent ventilated seats, and how manageable the truck feels despite its large size thanks to light steering assistance. The diesel engine provides strong performance with responsive turbo power, while the interior offers premium comfort and comprehensive technology features.

expertReviews.title: When You Need to Tow an Elephant | 2025 Ford F-250 Super Duty Review
pros: Class-leading towing capacity up to 23,000 lbs
Powerful 6.7L turbo diesel with 500 hp and 1,200 lb-ft torque
Spacious and luxurious interior with premium materials
Advanced towing features including Pro-Trailer system and onboard scale
Excellent visibility from elevated driving position
Comprehensive off-road Tremor package for $4,300
Power tailgate and convenient bed features
Pro Power onboard system with 2kW output
cons: Feels oversized and wide on narrow roads
Vague steering that tends to wander in lanes
Lane keep assist pulls to left side of lane
Elevated running boards make entry/exit more difficult
Bang & Olufsen audio system has distorted highs at high volume
Expensive - test truck cost $108,000 with options
Bouncy ride when unloaded
expertReviews.verdict: The 2025 Ford F-250 Super Duty is the leader in heavy-duty towing capacity and offers impressive technology features. While it feels every bit of its massive size on the road with vague steering and lane wandering, it delivers excellent power, luxury appointments, and comprehensive towing capabilities. The Tremor package adds serious off-road credentials. At $108K as tested, it's expensive but competitively priced against rivals, though Ram offers a smoother ride if maximum towing isn't needed.

expertReviews.title: Ford Super Duty F250 Pros And Cons
pros: Huge variety of trim levels from XL to Platinum with options for everyone
Tremor package includes front limited slip differential as standard unlike F-150
Four excellent engine options including 7.3L Godzilla gas and 6.7L Power Stroke diesel
Excellent bed design with integrated steps and low tie-down points
Manual locking hubs still available
Easy to fit 37-inch tires with minimal modifications
Chrome and blackout appearance packages available
Rear locker works in 2WD, 4WD high, and 4WD low
Can configure Tremor in multiple engine and trim combinations
cons: Poor shock placement location behind leaf springs
Extremely expensive LED taillight replacement costs around $4,000
Stingy on bed liner inclusion
Declining fit and finish quality with uneven panel gaps
Ford is tight on deals and incentives
High-end configurations can reach $100,000
expertReviews.verdict: The Ford Super Duty F-250 offers exceptional engine choices and trim variety, making it highly configurable for different needs and budgets. The 7.3L gas and 6.7L diesel engines are standouts in the heavy-duty segment. While quality control has declined and some parts are overpriced, the truck's capability and options make it a strong contender. A Tremor with XLT trim and 7.3L gas can be had for around $60,000 versus $100,000 for fully loaded versions.

expertReviews.title: Even SHE Wants to Daily Drive It // 2025 Ford F-250 Super ...
pros: Incredible storage space inside cabin
Excellent visibility from high seating position
Very comfortable seats with massage function
Impressive acceleration for 8,000lb diesel truck
Family-friendly with good back seat space
Physical controls for climate and key functions
Strong towing capability with 1,200 lb-ft torque
cons: Extremely difficult to park and maneuver in tight spaces
Requires significant space - hangs into street in normal driveway
Very expensive at $108,000
Challenging U-turns requiring multiple lanes
Chrome exterior may be too flashy for utility vehicle
Steering has lots of play requiring constant adjustments
expertReviews.verdict: The 2025 Ford F-250 Power Stroke is an impressively capable truck that excels in performance, comfort, and utility, but its massive size makes it challenging for everyday driving. While it offers exceptional torque, spacious interior, and family-friendly features, the difficulty parking and maneuvering in urban environments limits its practicality as a daily driver unless you specifically need its towing and hauling capabilities.

expertReviews.title: FORD F-250 6.7L PowerStroke | Do You NEED A 2500 Diesel ...
pros: Outstanding fuel economy (24.6L/100km vs much worse gas engines)
Exceptional torque delivery with 1,050 lb-ft
Stays in top gear on most hills with minimal effort
Excellent throttle response at low speeds
More stable towing due to heavier truck weight
Superior transmission cooling compared to 1500s
cons: Emission system reliability issues cause frequent check engine lights
Lower max towing capacity (15,500 lbs) than expected for price premium
Expensive upgrade cost over comparable 1500 trucks
Complex modern diesel systems less reliable than gasoline engines
expertReviews.verdict: The F-250 Power Stroke excels at towing with impressive fuel economy and effortless performance, but for 8,000 lb trailers, modern 1500s are sufficient. Only worth the upgrade for trailers over 10,000 lbs where you need the heavier platform, better cooling, and stronger components. Emission system reliability remains a concern.
